cat << EOF
KMuddy is a mud client designed for KDE. It's features include ANSI Color,
MSP, multiple connection, configurable colors, command history,
connection profiles, quick connect, auto-connect on startup, multi-line
input, aliases (with regex support), triggers (with regex support),
color triggers, special purpose triggers, prompt detection triggers,
gagging, alias/trigger groups, profile settings, speed-walking,
external scripting support, timers, macros, and variables.
EOF
